<BaseLayout title="About | LetsFixIndia" description="About the LetsFixIndia public record and how to help make it more accurate.">
  <div class="page-shell"><header class="record-header"><p class="eyebrow">About the project</p><h1>India leaves a paper trail.</h1><p class="lede">LetsFixIndia turns that trail into something easier to read, verify, and correct—one record at a time.</p></header>
    <div class="method-grid section"><article class="method-card"><h3>Not a verdict</h3><p>The site documents events, claims, outcomes, and unresolved questions. Readers should be able to see the difference.</p></article><article class="method-card"><h3>Receipts first</h3><p>Every useful claim needs a source a reader can inspect. Headlines are a starting point, not the end of the work.</p></article><article class="method-card"><h3>Built to be corrected</h3><p>Dates, legal outcomes, numbers, and wording can change when stronger evidence appears.</p></article><article class="method-card"><h3>Public by design</h3><p>The published record and its source ledger are designed for scrutiny, not passive consumption.</p></article></div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
